*jdmonthname*

(PHP 4, PHP 5, PHP 7)

jdmonthname â€” Returns a month name

===============================================================================
[ Description ]

  jdmonthname ( int $julianday , int $mode ) : string~

Returns a string containing a month name. {mode} tells this function which
calendar to convert the Julian Day Count to, and what type of month names are
to be returned.

                                Calendar modes
          Mode              Meaning                    Values
CAL_MONTH_GREGORIAN_SHORT Gregorian - Jan, Feb, Mar, Apr, May, Jun, Jul, Aug,
                          abbreviated Sep, Oct, Nov, Dec
                                      January, February, March, April, May,
CAL_MONTH_GREGORIAN_LONG  Gregorian   June, July, August, September, October,
                                      November, December
CAL_MONTH_JULIAN_SHORT    Julian -    Jan, Feb, Mar, Apr, May, Jun, Jul, Aug,
                          abbreviated Sep, Oct, Nov, Dec
                                      January, February, March, April, May,
CAL_MONTH_JULIAN_LONG     Julian      June, July, August, September, October,
                                      November, December
                                      Tishri, Heshvan, Kislev, Tevet, Shevat,
CAL_MONTH_JEWISH          Jewish      AdarI, AdarII, Nisan, Iyyar, Sivan,
                                      Tammuz, Av, Elul
                                      Vendemiaire, Brumaire, Frimaire, Nivose,
CAL_MONTH_FRENCH          French      Pluviose, Ventose, Germinal, Floreal,
                          Republican  Prairial, Messidor, Thermidor, Fructidor,
                                      Extra

===============================================================================
[ Parameters ]

{jday}

  The Julian Day to operate on

{mode}

  The calendar mode (see table above).

===============================================================================
[ Return Values ]

The month name for the given Julian Day and {mode}.


